In this speech, National Security Advisor Ambassador Robert O'Brien expresses gratitude for the support of the Zionist Organization of America (ZOA) and its members. He emphasizes the strong relationship between the United States and Israel, highlighting President Donald Trump's unprecedented support for Israel. O'Brien mentions key actions taken by the Trump administration, such as recognizing Jerusalem as the capital of Israel, opening the American Embassy in Jerusalem, and acknowledging Israeli sovereignty over the Golan Heights. He also discusses the administration's efforts to combat Iran's aggression, including withdrawing from the Iran nuclear deal, imposing tough sanctions, and pressuring Iran to end its nuclear program and support for terrorism. O'Brien reaffirms America's commitment to Israel's security and its right to self-defense. He concludes by praising the alliance between the United States and Israel, emphasizing the shared values of democracy, human dignity, and individual liberty.